comments: Robinson (NYK) establishes legal screening position firming up in Dotson's (CLE) path and makes some contact as they disengage.
Robinson (NYK) sets the screen on Dotson (CLE) from a wide stance and makes leg to leg contact that affects his ability to defend the play.
Dotson (NYK) applies a stayed hand to Barrett's (NYK) body and removes his hand as Barrett begins his upward shooting motion.
Bullock (NYK) makes marginal contact to Osman's (CLE) arm during his rip-through out on the perimeter and disengages.
Robinson (NYK) makes marginal contact with Drummond's (CLE) non-shooting arm as he retreats his arm to a vertical position and the contact does not affect his shot attempt.
Randle (NYK) straddles the lane line and is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Randle (NYK) makes some contact to Nance Jr.'s (CLE) chest as they engage for the loose ball and contact does not affect his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Drummond (CLE) makes incidental foot to ball contact during Barrett's (NYK) drive to the basket.
Randle (NYK) commits a clear path foul on Dotson (CLE).
Barrett (NYK) makes marginal contact to Dotson (CLE) defending his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Robinson (NYK) establishes legal screening position firming up in Steven's (CLE) path and makes some contact as they disengage.
Drummond (CLE) makes contact with Randle's (NYK) arm that affects his shot near the rim.
Randle (NYK) straddles the lane line and is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Bullock (NYK) extends his leg in Dotson's (CLE) path and makes foot to ball contact during his drive and a kicked ball violation is correctly called.
Bullock (NYK) cleanly deflects the pass attempt to Dotson (CLE). Any ensuing contact is deemed incidental.
There is no clear or conclusive angle that shows Bullock (NYK) steps out of bounds at the end of his drive to the basket.
Drummond (CLE) makes marginal contact with Robinson's (NYK) arm in the lane.
Robinson (NYK) commits a take foul on Drummond (CLE).
Robinson (NYK) establishes legal screening position in Dotson's (CLE) path and gives him a step to avoid contact.
Drummond (CLE) cleanly dislodges the ball from Barret (NYK).
Quickley (NYK) commits a take foul on Drummond (CLE).
Stevens (CLE) legally contests Quickley's (NYK) driving shot attempt.
Barrett (NYK) commits a take foul on Okoro (CLE).
